10.2.1
Clone a repository:
Cloning a repository is downloading a copy of the repository and all its contents such that you can make changes without directly affecting the original reposotory

10.2.2
Creating a branch:
Creating a branch of a repository is creating a second version of that repository that can be directly compared to the original.
In addition it is typically where a specific user make their changes to the code without affecting the code of any other thereby acting as a suggestion.

10.2.3
Commiting changes
Commiting changes is the action of saving a difference between your branch and the original master branch on your computer.

10.2.4
Pushing to the remote repository
Pushing to a remote repository is sending the branch from your computers branch to the remote storage of the code allowing it to be merged with the master branch.

